Manchester United forward Marcus Rashford has fired back at reports of a split in the Red Devils dressing room. The England international, 24, took to social media in response to claims of a rift among the English players and Cristiano Ronaldo at United. A journalist from German outlet BILD reported that the likes of Harry Maguire and Rashford are ‘irritated’ that Ronaldo wants to lead the squad with his ‘clique’. Portsmouth Sack 3 Players For Racist Messages About Rashford,… Euro 2020 Final Penalties: I ‘Won’t Apologise’… However, Rashford dismissed these claims as ‘made-up’ in a fiery response on Twitter. In response to the journalist’s tweet, he wrote: “Are we just making it up as we go along now then? Please stop looking for divides.” It comes after United’s players have been criticised for supposedly leaking information to the media. Club legend Gary Neville was furious after reports emerged to suggest one of Ralf Rangnick’s coaches has been nicknamed Ted Lasso by the players. United ended a run of three straight 1-1 draws with a timely 2-0 win over Brighton at Old Trafford on Tuesday night, leapfrogging West Ham into fourth. POLL The Seagulls dominated the first-half before Ronaldo delivered a moment of magic, ending a six-game drought. And Bruno Fernandes added a second after the visitors were reduced to ten men, easing some of the pressure on Rangnick and his players.